      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for the choice of hemolysis damage model (power-law vs mechanistic) including sensitivity analysis demonstrating model form uncertainty is bounded.",
      "rationale": "Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) selected without formal comparison to mechanistic alternatives. Model form uncertainty not quantified. Critical epistemic gap at MRL 5 given that hemolysis model selection dominates prediction uncertainty. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
    },
    {
