      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs characterised with probability distributions derived from patient population data; Monte Carlo UQ propagates full input uncertainty to hemolysis QoI.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed for 4 of 9 identified uncertain inputs; blood viscosity, red blood cell fragility, and inlet turbulence intensity distributions not characterised from patient data. Partial UQ coverage leaves input uncertainty underestimated. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
