  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-not-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors reviewed against MRL 5 requirements. Seven factors formally assessed; six flagged as epistemic gaps. Achieved levels fall below required levels across all assessed factors. The hemolysis model form uncertainty (factor: Model form) and incomplete Monte Carlo UQ coverage (factor: Model inputs) represent the most critical gaps for a Class III VAD submission. The assessment team notes that the methodology described in the referenced publication (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) was cited as the basis for the hemolysis damage model selection and UQ protocol; however, the local evidence package does not include a resolved node for this reference, and no external fetch hint is provided, leaving the methodological provenance unverifiable within the package graph. Despite this, the overall credibility package is accepted at Low assurance level pending resolution of all identified gaps in a future submission cycle.",
